---

# Health Guard App – Setup Guide

Full-stack Hospital Appointment System using:

* React (Frontend)
* Node.js + Express (Backend)
* Firebase Authentication
* Firestore Database
* Cloudinary (Image Upload)

---

# 1. Project Structure

```
health-guard-app
│
├── client        → React frontend
│
└── server        → Node backend
```

---

# 2. Required Software

Install:

### 1. Node.js

Download and install:

```
https://nodejs.org
```

Check installation:

```bash
node -v
npm -v
```

---

# 3. Clone Project

```bash
git clone https://github.com/nithiya1710-sri/health-guard-app.git

cd health-guard-app
```

---

# 4. Frontend Setup (React)

## Go to client folder

```bash
cd client
```

## Install packages

```bash
npm install
```

### Required packages

If missing install manually:

```bash
npm install axios
npm install firebase
npm install react-router-dom
```

Firebase Web SDK is installed via npm for web apps. ([Firebase][1])

---

# 5. Backend Setup (Node)

## Go to server folder

```bash
cd ../server
```

## Install packages

```bash
npm install
```

### Required packages

If needed:

```bash
npm install express
npm install cors
npm install dotenv
npm install firebase-admin
npm install multer
npm install cloudinary
npm install axios
```

Firebase Admin SDK is required for server authentication and database access. ([Firebase][2])

---

# 6. Firebase Setup

## Step 1 – Create Firebase Project

Go to:

```
Firebase Console
```

Create project.

Enable:

* Authentication → Email/Password
* Authentication → Google
* Firestore Database

---

# 7. Firebase Client Config

Location:

```
client/src/services/firebase.js
```

Example:

```js
import { initializeApp } from "firebase/app";
import { getAuth } from "firebase/auth";

const firebaseConfig = {

apiKey: "YOUR_KEY",
authDomain: "YOUR_DOMAIN",
projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
storageBucket: "YOUR_BUCKET",
messagingSenderId: "YOUR_ID",
appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"

};

const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

export const auth = getAuth(app);
```

---

# 8. serviceAccount.js Setup (IMPORTANT)

## Step 1 – Download Service Account File

Firebase Console →

```
Project Settings
```

→

```
Service Accounts
```

→

```
Generate New Private Key
```

Download JSON file.

This JSON file contains credentials used by the server to access Firebase. ([Stack Overflow][3])

---

## Step 2 – Save File

Save file in:

```
server/serviceAccount.js
```

OR

```
server/serviceAccountKey.json
```

Recommended structure:

```
server
│
├── serviceAccountKey.json
├── index.js
├── routes
└── package.json
```

---

# 9. serviceAccount.js Example

Location:

```
server/serviceAccount.js
```

```
const serviceAccount = require("./serviceAccountKey.json");

module.exports = serviceAccount;
```

---

# 10. Firebase Admin Initialization

Location:

```
server/index.js
```

Example:

```js
const admin = require("firebase-admin");

const serviceAccount = require("./serviceAccount");

admin.initializeApp({
credential: admin.credential.cert(serviceAccount)
});
```

Firebase Admin SDK must be initialized using the service account credentials. ([Stack Overflow][4])

---

# 11. Environment File (.env)

Location:

```
server/.env
```

Example:

```
PORT=5000

CLOUDINARY_NAME=xxxx
CLOUDINARY_KEY=xxxx
CLOUDINARY_SECRET=xxxx
```

---

# 12. Start Backend

Inside server folder:

```bash
npm start
```

OR

```bash
node index.js
```

Server runs on:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

# 13. Start Frontend

Open new terminal:

```bash
cd client
npm start
```

Runs on:

```
http://localhost:3000
```

---

# 14. Add serviceAccountKey.json to Git Ignore

Create or edit:

```
server/.gitignore
```

Add:

```
serviceAccountKey.json
.env
```

Service account keys should not be uploaded publicly. ([Medium][5])

---

# 15. Full Installation Commands

Run step-by-step:

```
git clone https://github.com/nithiya1710-sri/health-guard-app.git

cd health-guard-app

cd client
npm install

cd ../server
npm install

npm start
```

New terminal:

```
cd client
npm start
```

---

# 16. Default Ports

| Service | Port |
| ------- | ---- |
| React   | 3000 |
| Node    | 5000 |

